editMerge(25.10)                                              editMerge(25.10)

Name
       editMerge - Merges all of the same-width, layer, and net wires that are
       colinear with and electrically connected to the selected wire

Syntax
       editMerge

       [-help]

       [-select_only]

       Merges  all  of  the same-width, layer, and net wires that are colinear
       with and electrically connected to the selected wire.

       If -select_only is specified, the command merges the selected wires/ob-
       jects with each other.

       Note that editMerge:

              * Does not merge signal wires that contain branches.

              * Supports 45-degree wire edits as well.

              * Can also be used to merge selected bus guides.

       Note: Use the editSelectcommand to select the wire. Use the  selectBus-
       Guide command to select bus guides or segments.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  the  usage of the command. For a detailed description of
              the command, use the man command:

              man editMerge

       -select_only
              Specifies that only the selected wires should be merged.

